Hi all,

I am just wondering where it was first stated (for both directions) that th=
e category of coalgebras for a comonad on a Grothendieck topos E is again G=
rothendieck if and only if the underlying endofunctor of E is accessible.=20

A modern argument might go as: the topos of coalgebras is Grothendieck if a=
nd only if it is locally presentable if and only if the endofunctor is acce=
ssible, the original probably just mentioned preservation of filtered colim=
its.

Many thanks,

David Roberts=


